headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook tied Oscar Robertson’s NBA record for triple-doubles with 181, finishing with 33 points, 19 rebounds and 15 assists, and made two free throws with a second left to give Washington a 133-132 overtime victory over Indiana on Saturday...
headlines.shortLinkText: Westbrook ties Robertson's record, Wizards beat Pacers

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid scored 29 points, Tyrese Maxey added 22 and the Philadelphia 76ers won their eighth straight game, 118-104 over the Detroit Pistons on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 29, 76ers beat Pistons for 8th straight win

headlines.description: — Jonas Valanciunas had 18 points and 21 rebounds, De'Anthony Melton hit four 3-pointers in the fourth quarter, and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Toronto Raptors 109-99 Saturday night to move closer to a play-in spot.
headlines.shortLinkText: Valanciunas has double-double, Grizzlies beat Raptors 109-99

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 33 points, including five free throws over the last 21 seconds, and Kyrie Irving added 31 as the Brooklyn Nets snapped a four-game skid by storming back to beat the short-handed Denver Nuggets 125-119 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets rally to beat Nuggets 125-119, snap 4-game skid

headlines.description: — Georges Niang tied a career high with 24 points and the NBA-leading Utah Jazz beat the short-handed Houston Rockets 124-116 on Saturday night to reach 50 victories.
headlines.shortLinkText: NBA-leading Jazz beat Rockets 124-116 for 50th victory

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 49 points in 29 minutes and matched his season best with 11 3-pointers and the Golden State Warriors beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 136-97 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry makes 11 3s, scores 49 points to help Warriors roll

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard scored 30 points and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the San Antonio Spurs 124-102 on Saturday night, moving closer to an outright playoff spot.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard scores 30, Trail Blazers rout Spurs 124-102
